s very much a Mediterranean phenomenon. French and English authors wrote itineraries in the Holy Land, chronicles of the Crusades, and fanciful accounts of Christian knights who championed the Latin Church in the East. This study aims to explore the ways in which Iberian authors imagined their role in the culture of Crusade, both as participants and interpreters of narrative traditions of the crusading world from north of the Pyrenees.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCrusades in literature. 0aFiction, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 0aSpanish fictionyTo 1500xHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aBlaquerna, al-Andalus.  aCrusades Medieval Iberian Literature.  aFlores y Blancaflor.  aHoly Land.  aJoanot de Matorell.  aMediterranean Studies.  aTirant lo Blanc.  achronicles of the Crusades.  aliterary history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753134840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487531348423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487531348.jpg  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065206-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b201